<br>
For someone who is currently stuyding to become a physician, I found these &quot;addictive qualities&quot; facinating.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2002/10/17/48hours/main525965.shtml">www.cbsnews.com/stories/2...5965.shtml</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The unfortunate suicide of  Shawn Woolley last year was also featured, although I don't think EQ was entirely to blame.<br>
<br>
Liz Woolley (Shawn's mother) did make a very interesting observation I'd like to point out.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> by design. “I think the way the game is written is that when you first start playing it, it is fun, and you make great accomplishments. And then the further you get into it, the higher level you get, the longer you have to stay on it to move onward<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My family and friends still can't believe I spent 55+ hours of my real life to &quot;camp&quot; Rage Fire in SolB last year for my epic (big hugs to everyone who helped me with that!). <br>
<br>
One year later, upon reflection, it does sound pretty fugged up.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bottom line, EQ is &quot;just&quot; a computer game.  However, we all know the power of &quot;Evercrack&quot;.  When the game begins to interfere with one's daily &quot;routine&quot;: school, work, family and friends, and becomes a &quot;way of life&quot;, obviously an &quot;addiction&quot; of sorts has manifested itself. <br>
<br>
Just as with other sorts of recreational activites, alchohol, drugs, sex etc  &quot;too much of a good thing can harm you&quot;... well maybe not sex  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seriously though..we are all adults (well most of us) and I'm confident that most players know their limits and keep a healthy balance of EQ and RL.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately 48hrs portrayed EQ as this evil PC game. It is a pity they (CBS) couldn't have focused more on the positives of EQ such as the strong online friendships formed through cooperation, teamwork and working towards a common goal.<br>
<br>
Hmm think I'll go log in now  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
cheers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
