So until 48 hours sets up a help hotline for people addicted to TV during a program where they talk to the mother of someone who killed themselves with the TV on - I can't take them seriously as a news reporter. Hundreds of thousands more people are addicted to TV than are addicted to computer games. Being a news medium should require that you present an objective report... more and more US news isn't doing that from my point of view.  I have been turning to BBC and some other news sources. <br>
<br>
