<br>
When I am not on the PC I read a lot, or watch movies, or several other things that would fit into the category of addiction. <br>
<br>
But if someone is mentally retarded, has epilepsy, has been diagnosed with a disorder, shuts out their immediate family, and somehow obtains a gun.... 48hours didn't even point out some of those things like the police did, or other news sources did. The police investigating found no proof that everquest was connected. The only thing that's even close is that was on when they found him and his character was dead ... and hey we should all know that its pretty easy to die if you aren't at the controls in this game. <br>
<br>
So if someone with these problems kills themselves - even if it was proven as game related - that's a reason to condemn or slander a product ? Technically the 21 year old adult was likely using the product in violation of Sony's warning label for epilepsy.  <br>
<br>
I feel real bad that the person killed themselves - whatever the reasons were. But I just don't feel it was justified running a report on the addictive quality of an entertainment product without ALSO pointing out that all entertainment can be addictive - including the medium you are broadcasting the message on... <br>
